---
import MainNav from '../../components/MainNav.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <title>The Law of Return - Labyrinth</title>
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;600;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <style>
      :global(*) {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      :global(body) {
        margin: 0;
        min-height: 100vh;
        background:
          radial-gradient(circle at 24% 18%, rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.08), transparent 34%),
          radial-gradient(circle at 78% 72%, rgba(98, 98, 120, 0.08), transparent 34%),
          #050505;
        color: #aaaab8;
        font-family: "Cinzel", serif;
      }

      .chamber-shell {
        width: min(920px, calc(100% - 2rem));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem) 0 4rem;
      }

      .chamber {
        padding: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 3rem);
        border: 1px solid rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.24);
        border-radius: 10px;
        background: linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(12, 12, 14, 0.88), rgba(5, 5, 5, 0.96));
        box-shadow: 0 0 50px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.75), inset 0 0 50px rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.035);
      }

      .kicker {
        color: rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.72);
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.18rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        text-align: center;
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 0.8rem 0 1rem;
        color: #c4a76f;
        font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 7vw, 3.6rem);
        letter-spacing: 0.12rem;
        line-height: 1.08;
        text-align: center;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .lede {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto 2.2rem;
        color: rgba(170, 170, 184, 0.9);
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .law-list {
        display: grid;
        gap: 0.85rem;
        margin: 2rem 0;
      }

      .law {
        padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
        border-left: 2px solid rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.45);
        background: rgba(26, 26, 30, 0.5);
      }

      .law strong {
        display: block;
        color: #d2b982;
        margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
      }

      p {
        line-height: 1.75;
      }

      .seal {
        margin: 2.5rem auto 0;
        max-width: 620px;
        color: #d2b982;
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .return-link {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        margin-top: 2rem;
      }

      .return-link a {
        color: #c4a76f;
        text-decoration: none;
        border: 1px solid rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.32);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 0.7rem 1.1rem;
      }

      .return-link a:hover {
        background: rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.1);
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="chamber-shell">
      <MainNav />
      <main class="chamber">
        <div class="kicker">First Chamber</div>
        <h1>The Law of Return</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          The Labyrinth opens only after the first law is remembered: depth is not
          permission to abandon the center. The hand comes home before it reaches.
        </p>

        <section class="law-list" aria-label="Return laws">
          <article class="law">
            <strong>Return before reaching.</strong>
            The seeker must know how to come back before asking the deeper rooms to answer.
          </article>
          <article class="law">
            <strong>Presence before interpretation.</strong>
            No symbol, silence, artifact, or answer is handled cleanly until the room is met first.
          </article>
          <article class="law">
            <strong>State before solution.</strong>
            What has drifted matters. What is alive matters. Retrieval without orientation becomes flood.
          </article>
          <article class="law">
            <strong>Contact before content.</strong>
            The path is relational before it is informational. Access is not the same as worthiness.
          </article>
        </section>

        <p>
          This chamber is not a lock. It is a correction. It refuses the old habit of
          treating depth as a prize and mystery as a thing to seize. The Labyrinth is
          entered by steadiness, not hunger.
        </p>

        <p class="seal">
          A path that cannot return is not descent. It is loss with better lighting.
        </p>

        <nav class="return-link" aria-label="Labyrinth return">
          <a href="/labyrinth">Return to the Labyrinth</a>
        </nav>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
